ARIZONA PUBLIC SERVICE COMPANY
FERC Electric Tariff, Volume No. 7
Reserve Energy Tariff

ARIZONA PUBLIC SERVICE FERC Electric Tariff, Volume No. 7 Reserve Energy Tariff
1. Applicability This tariff governs the sale of Reserve Energy Service by Arizona Public Service (Seller).
2. Definitions:
a. Day-Ahead Price means the Mid-C Day Ahead Price or the Palo Verde Day- Ahead Price. b. ICE means Intercontinental Exchange, Inc., or any successor organization. c. Mid-C Day-Ahead Price means (a) for On-Peak Hours, the Mid-Columbia Day- Ahead Peak Daily Fixed Price published by ICE at www.theice.com, under the headings Market Data: Indices: Market: ICE OTC: Report: North American Power: Hub: Mid C Peak or any successor headings and (b) for Off-Peak Hours, the Mid-Columbia Day-Ahead Off-Peak Daily Fixed Price published by ICE at www.theice.com, under the headings Market Data: Indices: Market: ICE OTC: Report: North American Power: Hub: Mid C Off-Peak or any successor headings. d. NERC means the North American Electric Reliability Corporation, or a successor organization that is responsible for establishing reliability criteria and protocols. e. Off-Peak Hours means all hours ending 01:00 PPT through 06:00 PPT and hours ending 23:00 PPT through 24:00 PPT, Monday through Saturday and hours ending 01:00 PPT through 24:00 PPT, on Sundays and NERC designated holidays. f. On-Peak Hours means all hours ending 07:00 PPT through 22:00 PPT, Monday through Saturday, excluding NERC designated holidays. g. Palo Verde Day-Ahead Price means (a) for On-Peak Hours, the Palo Verde Day-Ahead Peak Daily Fixed Price published by ICE at www.theice.com, under the headings Market Data: Indices: Market: ICE OTC: Report: North American Power: Hub: Palo Verde Peak or any successor headings and (b) for Off-Peak Hours, the Palo Verde Day-Ahead Off-Peak Daily Fixed Price published by ICE at www.theice.com, under the headings Market Data: Indices: Market: ICE OTC: Report: North American Power: Hub: Palo Verde Off-Peak or any successor headings. h. Request Hour means the hour(s) during which the participant was delivered Reserve Energy Service. i. Reserve Energy Service means reserve energy provided pursuant to the Northwest Power Pool Reserve Sharing Program, or any successor procedure thereto. j. NWPP RSG Committee means the committee established under the terms of the NWPP Agreement to administer the NWPP Reserve Sharing Program. k. WECC Soft Price Cap means the price cap adopted by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission in San Diego Gas & Electric Company v. Sellers of Energy and Ancillary Services, 93 FERC ¶ 61,121 (2000) and Western Electric Coordinating Council, 133 FERC ¶ 61,026 (2010), subject to the guidance provided by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission in ConocoPhillips Company, et al., 175 FERC ¶ 61,226 (2021).
3. Availability Reserve Energy Service shall be available to any entity (Buyer) that has agreed to share reserves pursuant to the Northwest Power Pool Reserve Sharing Program, or any successor procedure thereto.
4. Rates Consistent with the Northwest Power Pool Reserve Sharing Program, settlement of Reserve Energy Service during the hour(s) which Reserve Energy Service is provided is at the Settlement Price, which shall be the average of Mid-C Day-Ahead Price and Palo Verde Day-Ahead Price for the Request Hour; provided, however, that if ICE does not publish a Day-Ahead Price for a relevant operating day or Request Hour, then the Settlement Price shall be the other Day-Ahead Price for the Request Hour and in no event will the Settlement Price be less than zero or greater than the WECC Soft Energy Price Caps in effect as of the Request Hour.
5. Billing and Settlements Financial Settlements will occur under the Sellers normal monthly billing cycle, unless otherwise mutually agreed.
